FBIS4-28703 "dreas113_a_94002" FBIS-EAS-94-113 Daily Report 11 Jun 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Reports on Issues Related to DPRK Continue Reports on Issues Related to DPRK Continue `Strong Possibility' of Resolution OW1106054994 Tokyo KYODO in English 0530 GMT 11 Jun 94 OW1106054994 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Hamamatsu, Shizuoka Prefecture, June 11 KYODO -- Japan's chief government spokesman said Saturday there is a strong possibility of the UN Security Council adopting a resolution in a week or 10 days against North Korea over the nuclear standoff. Chief Cabinet Secretary Hiroshi Kumagai made the comment in a speech in Hamamatsu. The Security Council is expected to begin debating next week a resolution the United States plans to submit calling for sanctions against North Korea because of its rejection of unhindered access to nuclear facilities suspected of being used for nuclear arms development.
